            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think this is a case of applying a setting to a projection that it was not meant to be used for.  The stereographic (or azimuthal in general) are not \"oblique\" in the sense I was thinking.  Oblique in GMT means that\r\n\r\n1. The map boundaries form a rectangle\r\n2. The boundaries are neither meridians nor parallels\r\n\r\nWith this definition, you see -JS \"fails\".\r\n\r\nShould not this be documented, you say? Well, yes...  I will have a look.\r\n",
